│ is in the `scalarizeBinopOrCmp` function in VectorCombine.cpp. The function │
│ attempts to scalarize vector operations with insertelement instructions,    │
│ but it doesn't check if the insertelement index is within bounds. When the  │
│ index is out of bounds (like index 3 for a 2-element vector), the original  │
│ code produces poison values, but the transformation creates a scalar        │
│ division by poison, which triggers undefined behavior.                      │
│                                                                             │
